Title : Ferdinand Joubert
Text : [[File:Guatemala 1871 Sc3.jpg|thumbnail|right|An 1871 stamp of Guatemala, engraved by Joubert.]]
'''Jean Ferdinand Joubert de la Ferté''' (1810–1884)<ref name=LP>"Joubert's Long Head as used for the Great Britain Revenue Stamps of 1855" by Malcolm J. Givans in ''[[The London Philatelist]]'', Vol. 123, No. 1414, April 2014, pp. 86-98.</ref> was a French [[engraver]], photographer and inventor who developed new photographic techniques and engraved notable [[Postage stamp|postage]] and [[revenue stamp]]s of the United Kingdom and the Confederate States. He was also the engraver of the [[Halfpenny Yellow]], the first postage stamp of Malta.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Bonnici|first1=A.|title=The Queen Victoria Malta Half Penny Yellow Postage Stamp|journal=Journal of the Malta Philatelic Society|date=December 2010|volume=39/3|page=4}}</ref>

== Life ==
Ferdinand Joubert was born in Paris on 15 September 1810.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oxfordartonline.com/view/10.1093/benz/9780199773787.001.0001/acref-9780199773787-e-00095962|title=Joubert, Ferdinand Jean {{!}} Benezit Dictionary of Artists|website=www.oxfordartonline.com|language=en|doi=10.1093/benz/9780199773787.article.b00095962|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref> He was a student of Henriquel-Dupont in 1829.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/research/search_the_collection_database/term_details.aspx?bioId=119506|title=Ferdinand Joubert (Biographical details)|last=|first=|date=|website=British Museum|language=en-GB|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref> Joubert married Francis Emelia in 1842.

